race.comment: AKA DAKA (7) is racing in fine form and looks to have found another suitable target here. He ran out a dominant winner when last seen at Echuca, albeit in a BM56, but has barely put a foot wrong this time in and John Allen takes over here. He'll put himself on speed and prove hard to run down again. HOUDINI (6) resumes. He mixed his form last time in but contested some stronger races than this. Zahra on suggests he should be ready to go from the good draw. COLOUR OUR WORLD (8) was okay last start at Sandown Lakeside in a handy race. The fresh win was solid and she's rarely far away. This looks a good option. LARIO (4) ran on well first up at Seymour to grab a narrow third and should be fitter. He is drawn to get back here but will be flashing late. LADY POTATO HEAD (3) conversely will be up on speed and can stick on.
